{"claim_id": "claim_005", "text": "pymzML supports reading indexed gzip files, which allows mzML file sizes to reach the levels of the original RAW format.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "One of the features of pymzML is the ability to (create) and read\nindexed gzip which allows mzML file sizes to reach the levels of the original\nRAW format.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [11166, 11303], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["pymzml_system"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_011", "text": "The igzip file format includes a comment field that stores unique IDs, version, index length, and offset length.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "This field is then used to save the Uniq IDs, version, index/offset length and is terminated with a zero byte", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [4959, 5068], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["arch_igzip_format"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_012", "text": "The GSGW and GSGR classes can be used to index any type of data beyond mzML files.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "However, the :py:func:`~pymzml.utils.GSGW.GSGW` and :py:func:`~pymzml.utils.GSGR.GSGR` class can be used to index any type of data.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [3906, 4038], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["pymzml_system", "comp_gsgw", "comp_gsgr"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_014", "text": "The GSGR class provides bracket notation access to retrieve indexed chapters from compressed files.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "one simply needs to initialize the :py:func:`~pymzml.utils.GSGR.GSGR` with the path to the created file and can access the chapters conveniently by the python bracket notation ([])", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [4600, 4780], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["pymzml_system", "comp_gsgr"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_036", "text": "The gzip format specification is defined in RFC 1952.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "For further information on the gzip format, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1952", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5025, 5085], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "citation", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_037", "text": "The igzip format includes a header with ID1, ID2, CM, FLG, MTIME, XFL, and OS fields.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "+-----+-----+----+-----+------------+-----+----+\n| ID1 | ID2 | CM | FLG | MTIME (x4) | XFL | OS |\n+-----+-----+----+-----+------------+-----+----+", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5105, 5186], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_038", "text": "The igzip format includes CRC32 and ISIZE fields at the end of compressed blocks.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "+---+---+---+----+---+---+---+----+\n|     CRC32 (x4) |     ISIZE (x4) |\n+---+---+---+----+---+---+---+----+", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5197, 5271], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_039", "text": "The igzip format comment field stores Index and Offset data terminated with a zero byte.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "+------------+------------+\n| Index (xX) | Offset (xX)|\n+------------+------------+\n\n...\n\n+------+\n| \\x00 |\n+------+", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_pymzml/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5334, 5409], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
